      "role": "user",
      "content": "i mean i guess, but it feels like that's just an excuse for politicians to win votes in certain states. if you look at the actual data, the costs to the average family usually outweigh those vague \"strategic\" benefits. so if a government decides to put tariffs on, are they basically just making a mistake that everyone knows is going to backfire?",
